# Planned Human-Subjects Study

This repository accompanies a paper whose results are derived entirely
from a **calibrated multi-agent simulation** (the MultiEthic-V benchmark).
As stated in Section 6.4 (Limitations) of the paper, an in-situ
human-subjects study is planned as the critical next step to validate
whether the simulated proxy gains (UES, BRI, UTS) transfer to real human
engagement and trust.

## Status

| Item | Status |
|---|---|
| IRB application | #IRB-2025-0311 — under review |
| Target platforms | Meta Horizon Worlds, Decentraland |
| Study design | Between-subjects, MEIA vs. B1/B4/B5 baselines |
| Target sample size | To be determined pending IRB approval and power analysis |

## What This Means for the Current Repository

All code, benchmarks, and results in this repository reflect the
**simulation study only**. No human-subject data is collected, stored, or
released as part of this repository. The demographic cohorts referenced
throughout the code (`A`-`E`) are simulation-internal behavioural cohort
labels calibrated to US Census Bureau population proportions — they do
not represent or derive from any real individual's demographic attributes.

## Future Updates

Upon IRB approval and completion of the human-subjects study, this
document and the repository will be updated with:
- A separate `human_study/` directory with the (de-identified, IRB-approved)
  analysis code
- An updated paper or follow-up publication reporting human-subject
  results
- Cross-references between simulated and human-validated metrics

Questions about the planned study can be directed to the corresponding
author via GitHub Issues on this repository.
